  "text": "Australia is similar to most developed nations in having well-functioning public and private health care systems. Universal health insurance is provided by Medicare, a system supported by the federal government [CITATION_1] . Veterinarians on the other hand almost wholly work in the private sector, either for individually owned private practices or for veterinary companies [31] . In 2006 10% of Australian veterinarians were employed by government, mainly in policy and administrative roles [31] .",
